library(ggplot2)
library(reshape2)
# Reading Data File
brainDF <- read.csv(".\\Brain.csv",header=TRUE,sep=",",
                       stringsAsFactors = TRUE, encoding = "UTF-8") # read data file
names(brainDF) <- c("Species","Brain","Body","Gestation","Litter")  # rename table columns

Step 1: Review Assumptions

Litter=brainDF$Litter  # Use for Legend
ggplot(brainDF,aes(x=brainDF$Gestation,y=brainDF$Brain,col=Litter))+geom_point()+
  labs(title = "Brain Weight vs Gestation",x="Gestation (days)",y="Brain Weight (g)")      # add axes titles

brainDF$logGestation <- log(brainDF$Gestation)
brainDF$logLitter <- log(brainDF$Litter)
brainDF$logBrain <- log(brainDF$Brain)

ggplot(brainDF,aes(x=brainDF$logGestation,y=brainDF$logBrain,col=Litter))+geom_point()+
  labs(title = "Log(Brain Weight) vs Log(Gestation)",x="Log(Gestation) (days)",y="Log(Brain Weight) (g)")      # add axes titles

Step 2: Build a Model

fit1 <- lm(brainDF$Brain ~ brainDF$Gestation + brainDF$Litter + brainDF$Body + brainDF$Gestation*brainDF$Litter, data=brainDF)
layout(matrix(c(1,2,3,4),2,2)) # optional 4 graphs/page 
plot(fit1)

The residuals are not random so we need to do a transformation.

fit2 <- lm(brainDF$Brain ~ brainDF$logGestation + brainDF$Litter + brainDF$Body + brainDF$Gestation*brainDF$Litter, data=brainDF)
layout(matrix(c(1,2,3,4),2,2)) # optional 4 graphs/page 
plot(fit2)

The residuals are still not random so we need to try a different transformation.

fit3 <- lm(brainDF$Brain ~ brainDF$Gestation + brainDF$logLitter + brainDF$Body + brainDF$Gestation*brainDF$Litter, data=brainDF)
layout(matrix(c(1,2,3,4),2,2)) # optional 4 graphs/page 
plot(fit3)

The residuals are still not random so we need to try a different transformation.

fit4 <- lm(brainDF$logBrain ~ brainDF$logGestation + brainDF$Litter + brainDF$Body + brainDF$logGestation*brainDF$Litter, data=brainDF)
layout(matrix(c(1,2,3,4),2,2)) # optional 4 graphs/page 
plot(fit4)

fit4.resids <- resid(fit4)            # store residuals of model
fit4.student.resids <- rstudent(fit4) # store studentized residuals of model

layout(matrix(c(1,2),1,2)) # optional 2 graphs/page 
hist(fit4.resids,main="Histogram of Residuals",xlab="Residuals")
hist(fit4.student.resids,main="Historgram of Studenized Residuals",xlab="Studenized Residuals")

The residuals appear random and the residual QQ plot appears linear.

We will use this model. Log(Brain) = Beta0 + Beta1Log(Gestation) + Beta2Litter + Beta3Body + Beta4Log(Gestation)*Litter

Step 3: Fit the Model

# Reading Data File
MF <- read.csv(".\\Meadowfoam Data.csv",header=TRUE,sep=",",
                       stringsAsFactors = TRUE, encoding = "UTF-8") # read data file
names(MF) <- c("Flowers", "Timing", "Intensity")  # rename table columns

# pred_u{flowers|Intensity}=Beta0 + Beta1*Intensity
summary(lm(Flowers~Intensity,data=MF))
